\def \articleABSTRACT{We attempt to reproduce results on a novel graph data mixup method called 'G-Mixup'. We investigate both theoretical and experimental claims on the effectiveness of G-Mixup to produce mixed-up synthetic graphs and to improve the performance of graph neural networks. Although we are able to reproduce some of the original paper's experimental results to within 6\% of their reported values, our results do not provide statistically significantly evidence that G-Mixup improves the performance of GNNs, nor does it perform better than other data augmentation methods.}
